The paper discusses the use of autoencoders, a popular technique in machine learning, for outlier detection. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of autoencoders in image processing, which suggests it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of neural networks to overfitting, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
